  23:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****   ==============================================================================
  24:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****                     ##### GPIO Peripheral features #####
  25:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****   ==============================================================================
  26:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****   [..]
  27:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****     (+) Each port bit of the general-purpose I/O (GPIO) ports can be individually
  28:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****         configured by software in several modes:
  29:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****         (++) Input mode
  30:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****         (++) Analog mode
  31:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****         (++) Output mode
ARM GAS  /tmp/cc5CGn6D.s 			page 2


  32:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****         (++) Alternate function mode
  33:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****         (++) External interrupt/event lines
  34:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c **** 
  35:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****     (+) During and just after reset, the alternate functions and external interrupt
  36:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****         lines are not active and the I/O ports are configured in input floating mode.
  37:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c **** 
  38:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****     (+) All GPIO pins have weak internal pull-up and pull-down resistors, which can be
  39:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****         activated or not.
  40:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c **** 
  41:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****     (+) In Output or Alternate mode, each IO can be configured on open-drain or push-pull
  42:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****         type and the IO speed can be selected depending on the VDD value.
  43:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c **** 
  44:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****     (+) The microcontroller IO pins are connected to onboard peripherals/modules through a
  45:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****         multiplexer that allows only one peripheral alternate function (AF) connected
  46:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****        to an IO pin at a time. In this way, there can be no conflict between peripherals
  47:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****        sharing the same IO pin.
  48:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c **** 
  49:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****     (+) All ports have external interrupt/event capability. To use external interrupt
  50:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****         lines, the port must be configured in input mode. All available GPIO pins are
  51:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****         connected to the 16 external interrupt/event lines from EXTI0 to EXTI15.
  52:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c **** 
  53:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****     (+) The external interrupt/event controller consists of up to 28 edge detectors
  54:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****         (16 lines are connected to GPIO) for generating event/interrupt requests (each
  55:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****         input line can be independently configured to select the type (interrupt or event)
  56:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****         and the corresponding trigger event (rising or falling or both). Each line can
  57:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****         also be masked independently.
  58:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c **** 
  59:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****                      ##### How to use this driver #####
  60:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****   ==============================================================================
  61:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****   [..]
  62:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****     (#) Enable the GPIO AHB clock using the following function: __HAL_RCC_GPIOx_CLK_ENABLE().
  63:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c **** 
  64:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****     (#) Configure the GPIO pin(s) using HAL_GPIO_Init().
  65:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****         (++) Configure the IO mode using "Mode" member from GPIO_InitTypeDef structure
  66:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****         (++) Activate Pull-up, Pull-down resistor using "Pull" member from GPIO_InitTypeDef
  67:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****              structure.
  68:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****         (++) In case of Output or alternate function mode selection: the speed is
  69:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****              configured through "Speed" member from GPIO_InitTypeDef structure.
  70:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****         (++) In alternate mode is selection, the alternate function connected to the IO
  71:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****              is configured through "Alternate" member from GPIO_InitTypeDef structure.
  72:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****         (++) Analog mode is required when a pin is to be used as ADC channel
  73:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****              or DAC output.
  74:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****         (++) In case of external interrupt/event selection the "Mode" member from
  75:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****              GPIO_InitTypeDef structure select the type (interrupt or event) and
  76:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****              the corresponding trigger event (rising or falling or both).
  77:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c **** 
  78:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****     (#) In case of external interrupt/event mode selection, configure NVIC IRQ priority
  79:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****         mapped to the EXTI line using HAL_NVIC_SetPriority() and enable it using
  80:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****         HAL_NVIC_EnableIRQ().
  81:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c **** 
  82:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****     (#) To get the level of a pin configured in input mode use HAL_GPIO_ReadPin().
  83:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c **** 
  84:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****     (#) To set/reset the level of a pin configured in output mode use
  85:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****         HAL_GPIO_WritePin()/HAL_GPIO_TogglePin().
  86:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c **** 
  87:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****    (#) To lock pin configuration until next reset use HAL_GPIO_LockPin().
  88:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c **** 
ARM GAS  /tmp/cc5CGn6D.s 			page 3


  89:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****     (#) During and just after reset, the alternate functions are not
  90:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****         active and the GPIO pins are configured in input floating mode (except JTAG
  91:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****         pins).
  92:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c **** 
  93:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****     (#) The LSE oscillator pins OSC32_IN and OSC32_OUT can be used as general purpose
  94:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****         (PC14 and PC15, respectively) when the LSE oscillator is off. The LSE has
  95:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****         priority over the GPIO function.
  96:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c **** 
  97:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****     (#) The HSE oscillator pins OSC_IN/OSC_OUT can be used as
  98:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****         general purpose PF0 and PF1, respectively, when the HSE oscillator is off.
  99:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g0xx_hal_gpio.c ****         The HSE has priority over the GPIO function.
